HEADWORD: Trochus
<hw>Tro"chus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Trochi</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ a
wheel.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous species of
marine univalve shells belonging to <gen>Trochus</gen> and many allied
genera of the family <fam>Trochidae</fam>. Some of the species are
called also <altname>topshells</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
